ALCOHOL CONTAMINATION, FATAL - RUSSIA (09)
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: 30 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail Mod.NR<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: IA Trud [edited]
<http://info.trud.ru/issue/shortnews.php?id=43389>


The number of casualties from surrogate alcohol is increasing in
Russia. Some specialists consider this an epidemic.

The number of cases country-wide is reaching 3000, ITAR-TASS reports.
In the Belgorod region more than 900 cases have been recorded, with
45 fatalities. There are about 800 registered cases in the Irkutsk
region, 33 of which died. Meanwhile, during the last several days
about 100 patients have been admitted to the hospitals in this region
[Irkutsk?]; an emergency situation is being announced in 14 cities
and districts.

There have been 400 cases in the Pskov region, with 16 fatalities.
Poisoning cases from faulty alcohol have also been recorded in Kirov,
Perm, Volgograd, Sverdlovsk, and Saratov regions.

******
[2]
Date: 30 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail Mod.NR<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: IA Trud [edited]
<http://info.trud.ru/issue/shortnews.php?id=43380>


Nine people died from alcohol poisoning in the Perm area. Currently
there are 210 patients with poisoning, 147 of whom have been
diagnosed with toxic hepatitis. This information comes from the
territorial office of Rospotrebnadzor, and reported by ITAR-TASS.

The head of the press relations office, Olga Shutova, says that the
most severe situation is in the Kungur region, where 6 of 9 fatal
cases [2/3 of cases are fatal?] and the biggest number of cases (134)
has been registered.

Law enforcement inspected more than 100 drug stores and shops; 194
lots of alcohol-containing products have been impounded, and 336
charges of administrative delinquency have been opened. The militia
of the region has been ordered to assess every case of poisoning very
carefully. Two criminal cases have already begun and 6 others are
under investigation.

